Package: growkar
Title: High-Throughput Microbial Growth Curve Analysis and Phenotyping
Version: 0.99.0
Authors@R: 
    person("Pooja", "Sethiya", 
           email = "poojasethiya24@gmail.com", 
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0001-6584-3912"))
Description: growkar provides infrastructure and statistical tools for the
    analysis of high-throughput microbial growth curve experiments, such as
    plate-based optical density (OD) assays. The package supports data
    import, quality control, normalization, and modeling of growth dynamics,
    enabling extraction of biologically meaningful phenotypes including lag
    time, growth rate, doubling time, and carrying capacity. growkar
    integrates with Bioconductor data structures, including
    SummarizedExperiment, allowing seamless incorporation of growth
    phenotypes with transcriptomic, genomic, and other omics datasets. This
    enables downstream multi-omics analysis and functional interpretation in
    microbial systems.
